      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JACKPOT JACK (2) had the drop on the lead and went on to be beaten 4.5 lengths into third (17.31) at this track in a Grade 5 over 300m. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Deserves serious consideration. WALK ME DADDY (8) missed the frame and safely held latest finishing 6th at Grafton following on from a win (17.24) at this track the start prior. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. In the mix. OCCITANIE (1) is worth forgiving last start after finishing fourth (24.19) from Box 7 at this track over 411m. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Has ability and can measure up. FEDERAL ESCAPE (7) can sneak into the finish.",
